{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_201","type":"agent_message","text":"I have a likely root cause now: `System.load(file)` goes through global `NativeLibrarySupport`, while JNI method resolution uses `ClassLoader.findNative(...)`. If those two registries stay separate in this runtime mode, the library can load successfully and the native symbol still won’t resolve. I’m confirming that lookup path in `ClassLoader.findNative` directly before I decide whether this is still fixable via metadata."}}
