{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_204","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve confirmed part of the runtime mismatch: in this GraalVM build, `ClassLoader.loadLibrary(Class, File)` is substituted to call global `NativeLibrarySupport.loadLibraryAbsolute(...)`, while JNI method resolution still goes through `ClassLoader.findNative(...)`. That means the remaining failure may be in GraalVM’s loader association rather than in our metadata file. I’m checking the repo’s other HawtJNI-based library (`jansi`) as a control case before I decide whether this run has reached a genuine runtime blocker."}}
